    title: 'World Sauna Forum Returns to Finland in June 2026',
    slug: 'world-sauna-forum-2026-jyvaskyla',
    dek: 'The global sauna industry\'s signature gathering heads to Jyvaskyla, with Sauna Region Week extending the programming to nine days.',
    excerpt: 'The World Sauna Forum 2026 will take place June 9-11 in Jyvaskyla, Finland, with the surrounding Sauna Region Week running June 6-14. The event, organized by Sauna from Finland, brings together manufacturers, designers, researchers, and operators for three days of talks, networking, and authentic Finnish sauna experiences.',
    contentType: 'Daily Brief',
    category: 'Manufacturer News',
    tags: ['World Sauna Forum', 'events', 'Finland', 'Jyvaskyla', 'Sauna from Finland'],
    author: authors.elise,
    publishDate: '2026-04-05',
    readingTime: 3,
    featuredImage: 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1749561532058-c4ad5fd00229?w=1200&q=80',
    body: `<p>The <a href="https://worldsaunaforum.com/" target="_blank">World Sauna Forum</a>, organized by <a href="https://saunafromfinland.com" target="_blank">Sauna from Finland</a>, is heading to Jyvaskyla for its 2026 edition. The three-day event (June 9-11) bills itself as "the most relaxing business event in the world," and based on past years, it delivers on that promise.</p>

<h2>What to Expect</h2>
<p>The forum brings together sauna manufacturers, wellness operators, architects, researchers, and enthusiasts from around the world for keynote talks, panel discussions, and what is probably the highest concentration of different sauna types you'll find in one place. Past speakers have included <a href="/article/sauna-immune-system-research-laukkanen">Professor Jari Laukkanen</a>, the University of Eastern Finland researcher whose longitudinal sauna studies have been published in JAMA Internal Medicine.</p>

<p>This year's event is part of a broader <strong>Sauna Region Week</strong> (June 6-14), which extends programming across the Jyvaskyla region with public sauna experiences, from the world's largest smoke sauna to traditional Finnish saunas with full bathing rituals.</p>

<div class="callout">
<strong>2026 Sauna Industry Events Calendar:</strong>
<ul>
<li>April 25: World Sauna Day (global)</li>
<li>June 6-14: Sauna Region Week (Jyvaskyla, Finland)</li>
<li>June 9-11: World Sauna Forum (Jyvaskyla, Finland)</li>
<li>September 24-26: XIX International Sauna Congress (Oslo, Norway)</li>
<li>October 6-8: Interbad 2026 (Stuttgart, Germany)</li>
</ul>
</div>

<h2>Why It Matters</h2>
<p>For anyone in the sauna business, the World Sauna Forum is the closest thing the industry has to an annual gathering of its global leadership. The networking alone is worth the trip. Tickets and details are available at <a href="https://worldsaunaforum.com/tickets/" target="_blank">worldsaunaforum.com</a>.</p>`,
